BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260426T094200
DTEND:20260426T174800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.953ft at 09:42\n-2.968ft at 17:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Morning starts off slow\, then a new pulse of longer period swell from for
 mer Typhoon Sinlaku will be moving in. That's good for waist to chest+ sur
 f over the afternoon\, showing largest late. Early morning high tide bogs 
 down tide sensitive spots\, then better shape follows much of the morning 
 as the tide ebbs out. Incoming tide push gets an assist much of the aftern
 oon.\n\nSW shifting WSW winds through the day\, for some manageable crumbl
 e. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260427T103600
DTEND:20260427T180600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.982ft at 10:36\n-2.968ft at 18:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Mid-period WNW swell\, along with a little lingering S swell\, is still go
 od for waist to chest high surf in the morning\, then waves gradually tape
 r off during the afternoon. Mid morning high tide slows tide sensitive bre
 aks. Ebbing tide through mid day helps.\n\nLight/variable morning winds\, 
 followed by a light+ SSW-SW sea breeze in the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260428T061800
DTEND:20260428T071200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.191ft at 06:18\n-2.944ft at 07:12\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Old combo of WNW swell and selective S swell fades to mainly thigh-waist h
 igh leftovers. Mid morning high tide slows the smaller waves. Ebbing tide 
 helps a bit through mid day. \n\nLight/variable winds in the morning\, shi
 ft to a light+ SW afternoon sea breeze. 
END:VEVENT
